# .gitleaksignore - Gitleaks exclusion patterns for Dev-AID
#
# This file excludes known false positives from secret scanning.
# All excluded patterns contain FAKE/EXAMPLE credentials for:
# - Educational purposes (anti-pattern documentation)
# - Test fixtures (pytest conftest, test files)
# - Code examples in skills/documentation
#
# IMPORTANT: These are NOT real secrets. They are intentionally included
# in the codebase to teach security best practices and enable testing.
#
# Last reviewed: 2025-12-10
# Review frequency: Quarterly (or when new skills/tests are added)

# ============================================================================
# TEST FILES - Fake credentials for pytest fixtures
# ============================================================================
# Why excluded: Test files use hardcoded fake API keys like
# "test-api-key-1234567890" to simulate real API interactions in tests.
# These are never used in production and are clearly marked as test data.

.dev-aid/orchestration/tests/**
**/test_*.py
**/conftest.py
**/tests/*.py

# ============================================================================
# ANTI-PATTERN DOCUMENTATION - Educational examples of BAD security practices
# ============================================================================
# Why excluded: These files intentionally show INSECURE code examples to teach
# developers what NOT to do. Examples include:
# - Hardcoded Stripe keys (sk_live_xxx) - demonstrating secret exposure
# - Plaintext passwords in YAML - demonstrating config vulnerabilities
# - Curl commands with auth headers - demonstrating credential leakage
#
# These are pedagogical tools, not actual credentials.

**/anti-patterns.md
**/references/anti-patterns.md
.dev-aid/providers/claude/.claude/skills/expert/*/references/anti-patterns.md

# ============================================================================
# SKILL DOCUMENTATION - Code examples and implementation patterns
# ============================================================================
# Why excluded: Skill files (SKILL.md) contain example code snippets showing
# both secure and insecure patterns. These may include:
# - API integration examples with placeholder keys
# - Security implementation examples with fake tokens
# - Configuration examples with example credentials
#
# All examples use obviously fake values (e.g., "example-key", "test-token").

**/SKILL.md
.dev-aid/providers/claude/.claude/skills/expert/*/SKILL.md
.dev-aid/skills/expert/*/SKILL.md

# ============================================================================
# BACKUP FILES - Temporary documentation backups during skill development
# ============================================================================
# Why excluded: Backup files (.backup, .backup-condense) are temporary copies
# created during skill refactoring. They contain the same example code as the
# original SKILL.md files and should be excluded for the same reasons.
#
# Note: These should be gitignored in the future (see .gitignore update).

**/SKILL.md.backup
**/SKILL.md.backup-*
*.backup
*.backup-condense

# ============================================================================
# SECURITY EXAMPLES - Demonstration of secure/insecure patterns
# ============================================================================
# Why excluded: These files show side-by-side comparisons of secure vs insecure
# code. The "insecure" examples necessarily include fake secrets to demonstrate
# vulnerabilities like:
# - Hardcoded credentials (to show why they're bad)
# - Weak encryption keys (to demonstrate key management issues)
# - Exposed tokens (to illustrate token handling best practices)

**/security-examples.md
**/references/security-examples.md

# ============================================================================
# CORE IMPLEMENTATION PATTERNS - Framework-specific examples
# ============================================================================
# Why excluded: These files provide copy-paste ready code snippets for common
# patterns. Some may include placeholder API keys in example configurations
# (e.g., FastAPI settings with EXAMPLE_API_KEY="changeme").

**/core-implementation-patterns.md
**/references/core-implementation-patterns.md

# ============================================================================
# TEMPORARY DEVELOPMENT FILES - Work-in-progress skill templates
# ============================================================================
# Why excluded: The temp/ directory contains drafts and templates during skill
# development. These aggregate multiple examples and may contain duplicated
# fake credentials from various sources.
#
# Note: temp/ should not be committed to git (recommend adding to .gitignore).

temp/**
temp/*.md
**/SKILL_AGENT_TEMPLATE.md

# ============================================================================
# DOCUMENTATION ARCHITECT COMMANDS - Example curl commands with fake tokens
# ============================================================================
# Why excluded: Documentation generation commands include example API calls
# with fake Bearer tokens (e.g., curl -H "Authorization: Bearer example-token").
# These demonstrate API authentication patterns for documentation purposes.

.dev-aid/providers/claude/.claude/commands/documentation/*.md
.dev-aid/providers/claude/.claude/agents/documentation/*.md

# ============================================================================
# REVIEW PROCESS
# ============================================================================
# To verify exclusions are still valid:
# 1. Run: grep -r "api.key\|api_key\|sk_live\|Bearer" <excluded-path>
# 2. Manually inspect flagged secrets
# 3. Confirm they are clearly fake (e.g., "test-", "example-", "1234567890")
# 4. Update this file if new patterns emerge
#
# To test Gitleaks still catches real secrets:
# 1. Temporarily add a real-looking secret to a non-excluded file
# 2. Run: gitleaks detect --source . --verbose
# 3. Verify detection works
# 4. Remove test secret
#
# Quarterly review checklist:
# [ ] Verify excluded paths still contain only fake/example credentials
# [ ] Check for new test files or documentation that should be excluded
# [ ] Ensure temp/ and *.backup files are not committed to git
# [ ] Test Gitleaks with a real-looking secret in a non-excluded path
